      public MovementTribute(String newName, String newDescription, int newPP, int newPower, int newPrecision, PokemonType newPT, TributeEffect estado, int newpPriority)
      Constructor for creating a new MovementTribute
      Parameters:
      newName - The name of the movement
      newDescription - A description of what the movement does
      newPP - The initial Power Points (PP) available for this movement
      newPower - The base power of the movement
      newPrecision - The accuracy percentage of the movement
      newPT - The elemental type of the movement
      estado - The tribute effect that will be applied to the target
      newpPriority - The priority level of the movement in battle

    • doAttackTo

      public int doAttackTo(Pokemon attacker, Pokemon target) throws PoobkemonException
      Executes the tribute attack from one Pokemon to another. Unlike regular attacks, this primarily applies an effect to the target rather than dealing significant damage. The attack has a chance to miss based on precision.
      Specified by:
      doAttackTo in interface Attackable
      Overrides:
      doAttackTo in class SpecialMovement
      Parameters:
      attacker - The Pokemon performing the attack
      target - The Pokemon receiving the attack
      Returns:
      The base damage value (usually minimal)
      Throws:
      PoobkemonException - MISSED_MOVEMENT if accuracy check fails
